(11, 2111, 'mrs. french', 'tracifrench@mac.com', 'http://blissfulb.blogspot.com', '97.120.221.62', '2009-10-28 11:31:41', '2009-10-28 16:31:41', 'loving each and everything here!  oh and why haven\'t we met yet!  xo t', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(12, 2111, 'knack', 'barb@knackstudios.com', 'http://www.knackstudios.com', '68.119.224.232', '2009-11-22 16:19:43', '2009-11-22 21:19:43', 'love these pieces by circa....especially the sauce bowls!\n\nxo', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(13, 2111, 'elsa', 'elsa@elsasam.com', 'http://www.elsasam.com', '98.246.173.230', '2009-11-28 22:41:22', '2009-11-29 03:41:22', 'Hope you can stop in the shop sometime. It would be lovely to meet you!', 0, '1', '', '', 11, 2),
(14, 2181, 'Jon', 'jbscmt@yahoo.com', '', '71.134.126.94', '2009-11-03 13:18:30', '2009-11-03 18:18:30', 'The moths &amp; tires is my favorite!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(15, 2554, 'eva / sycamore street press', 'eva@sycamorestreetpress.com', 'http://evajorgensen.blogspot.com', '166.70.214.13', '2010-01-17 00:46:29', '2010-01-17 05:46:29', 'have a great trip!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(16, 2572, 'Amanda', 'amanda@plyley.name', 'http://www.facebook.com/amanda.plyley', '67.40.255.1', '2010-02-12 16:34:41', '2010-02-12 21:34:41', 'Those Neapolitan chocolates are GOOD! and the Dovetail bike mugs were a big hit as an early valentine. Thanks for the fun shopping yesterday! :)', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(17, 2572, 'elsa', 'elsa@elsasam.com', 'http://www.elsasam.com', '72.11.120.233', '2010-02-12 16:52:49', '2010-02-12 21:52:49', 'So great to chat with you yesterday! Enjoy the goodies and hope to see you again soon! :)', 0, '1', '', '', 16, 2),
(18, 2681, 'Karen Vitt', 'neatsheet@karenvitt.com', 'http://pdxneatsheet.com', '67.171.139.89', '2010-04-13 17:42:33', '2010-04-13 22:42:33', 'Oooh, I love the whale mug! I\'m also all about your Octopus ceramics, which we wrote about today on my site. I don\'t think you have a facebook page, but I wanted you to see the link!\n\nhttp://pdxneatsheet.com/neat-trend/portland-fashion-octopus-motif-spring-2010/', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(19, 2681, 'elsa', 'elsa@elsasam.com', 'http://www.elsasam.com', '72.11.120.233', '2010-04-13 17:57:40', '2010-04-13 22:57:40', 'Thank you for sharing! :) \nWe do have a facebook page under "elsa+sam". I will be sure to post your link to the page! Thank you!', 0, '1', '', '', 18, 2),
(20, 3072, 'Antonia Jenkins', 'antoniawj@gmail.com', '', '71.111.123.182', '2010-08-24 21:44:39', '2010-08-25 02:44:39', 'I love to read your Elsa + Sam news!  Maybe you can blog along with Bennett\'s stages, and as you introduce him to the crockery, you can let your customers in on the results!  Great to follow, and wonderful advertising for you, the modern urban mom, and a way to keep Elsa + Sam fresh and fun!  Plus, if you have pictures and text, you can publish a very cool children\'s book!\n\nI want to come and hang out with you soon!  If you need any help, let me know-otherwise I\'ll just come and bother you while you try to get everything together!\n\nLove you!  xoxoxo', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(21, 3072, 'Lisa', 'info@hopitup.com', '', '75.150.47.129', '2010-08-25 17:45:23', '2010-08-25 22:45:23', 'We\'ve so enjoyed shopping at your beautiful store and we\'ll definitely be using your delivery service! Best of luck on the new adventure!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(22, 3072, 'Kim', 'kimberhorst@hotmail.com', '', '76.115.156.211', '2010-08-26 15:58:28', '2010-08-26 20:58:28', 'Dearest elsa, sam, et al,\n\nIt was a wonderful experience to drop by the store when in PDX and say hi, and make a new friend. I\'ll enjoy checking out the website and purveying the beautiful handcrafted and exotic + local flair-filled items you have available. \n\nLooking forward to seeing you whenever - and best wishes and luck - love the picture so much !!!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(23, 3072, 'Viviana', 'vivideLoera@gmail.com', 'http://cosmopolitansugar.blogspot.com/', '24.202.193.104', '2010-09-02 10:27:51', '2010-09-02 15:27:51', 'Hello from Montréal,\n\nI am sorry you have to close the shop, but I have a really good feeling about your upcoming website.  If it wasn\'t because of your store, Mark and I would have never met you, so do not close shop with a bitter sweet taste in your mouth, but with a big smile and positive thoughts.  Good things are coming for you and the tiny new addition...a boy!! Wow, Zach must be super excited.\nI look forward to your online store and I will be more than happy to write about it (and shop) in my blog. I miss Portland.  If I am in town, I will definitely contact you.    Check out  how are renovation project is coming along her:   http://pinterest.com/vivideloera/not-for-construction\n \n\nUn beso muy grande!!!\n\n\nViviana', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(24, 3072, 'Sweet Ronit', 'sweetronitpdx@gmail.com', 'http://sweetronit.com/blog', '24.20.46.237', '2010-09-03 08:44:55', '2010-09-03 13:44:55', 'Elsa!\n\nI will miss your shop so much - what but exciting changes in store! Congratulations!!!\n\nYou know I\'ll be looking around your new shop - but I\'ll miss our chats as I do so. Which makes me think, we\'re due! I\'ll be heading that way later and will stop by...\n\nAll the best!\n\nRonit', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(25, 3072, 'becki', 'editor@shoppingsmycardio.com', 'http://www.shoppingsmycardio.com', '98.246.147.215', '2010-09-13 11:17:01', '2010-09-13 16:17:01', 'hey elsa...was just thinking of you and wanted to check in. can\'t believe all the changes in your life this year, but they\'re exciting ones, to be sure!  congratulations on everything :)  xo', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(26, 3072, 'elsa', 'elsa@elsasam.com', 'http://www.elsasam.com', '98.246.173.230', '2010-09-14 10:59:13', '2010-09-14 15:59:13', 'Thank you everyone for the sweet messages! Even though we are thrilled with the new change, one thing I will miss is seeing my customers face to face & having great conversations. Because of the shop I\'ve had the opportunity to meet so many wonderful people &  I am grateful to have had the opportunity to meet all of you. XO!\nP.s. Now I must focus on naps before November arrives.. haha!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 2),
(27, 3072, 'Eva / Sycamore Street Press', 'eva@sycamorestreetpress.com', 'http://www.sycamorestreetpress.com', '71.35.226.228', '2010-09-27 14:39:15', '2010-09-27 19:39:15', 'Elsa, Kirk told me about the shop closing and the baby on the way! Although I\'m sad you have to close the shop before I was able to take a trip to PDX and see it, it\'s great you are able to keep the online shop. And I\'m so happy for you and your baby! (I guess Kirk told you we are also having our first in November?)', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(28, 3072, 'elsa', 'elsa@elsasam.com', 'http://www.elsasam.com', '98.246.173.230', '2010-09-28 12:45:14', '2010-09-28 17:45:14', 'Congrats to you, Eva! We are due within days of each other. Our due date is November 13th and we are expecting a boy. :) Hopefully next time you two cruise through town, we could have the lil\' ones meet. :) Best of luck to you!!!', 0, '1', '', '', 27, 2),
(29, 3072, 'kippi', 'kippil@msn.com', '', '209.180.170.205', '2010-09-30 19:34:28', '2010-10-01 00:34:28', 'hi went to pick up some wine today;missed our chat.hope you are feeling well.the dude is coming in about a month and a half.!!!!!!!!!!take care kippi', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(30, 3072, 'elsa', 'elsa@elsasam.com', 'http://www.elsasam.com', '98.246.173.230', '2010-10-01 11:44:26', '2010-10-01 16:44:26', 'Hi Kippi!\nI hope you\'re doing well! It\'s weird to see the old space fully transformed but I think it looks great. Miss our chats too! We\'re getting ready for the lil\' one... my goodness... so soon, so soon! xoxo!', 0, '1', '', '', 29, 2),
(31, 3304, 'Antonia Jenkins', 'antoniawj@gmail.com', '', '71.111.123.182', '2010-09-25 10:56:43', '2010-09-25 15:56:43', 'Hi Elsa+Zach!  Congrats on your new Web biz!  The pictures look great! xoxo', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(32, 3514, 'Viviana', 'vivideLoera@gmail.com', 'http://cosmopolitansugar.blogspot.com/', '74.56.38.48', '2011-11-21 07:04:53', '2011-11-21 15:04:53', 'Elsa!  Looks Good.  I wish you the best of luck.  I miss visiting your cozy shop.  Any plans to have a store again in the near future?  I know, its expensive.  If I win the lottery, I will help you set shop again.  I suppose I should start playing.\nI don\'t know if you\'re already familiar with them, but I recently came across two great magazines for moms and children that I fell in love with...  \nThey are MILK (http://www.milkmagazine.net/) + MILK Japan (http://milkjapon.com/) &amp; Papier Mache (http://www.papier-mache.com.au/).\nMark and I don\'t have kids yet but maybe soon.\n\nAnyway, Montreal is beautiful but cold.\n\nHappy Thanksgiving!\n\nViviana', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0) ;
