(39, 1, '2014-10-18 17:31:59', '2014-10-18 17:31:59', '<h2>\r\n	Here are a few of the nice things that folks have said about us!</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Gray Magazine Issue #2, February/March 2012<br />\r\n	<a href="http://issuu.com/graymag/docs/gray_magazine_issue_no._3/35">Inspired</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Portland Picks Writers\' Favorites of 2009!<br />\r\n	<a href="http://www.portlandpicks.com/newsletter/0308.php">#4: Doing the Dishes</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Willamette Week Retail Therapist, November 6th, 2009<br />\r\n	<a href="http://blogs.wweek.com/retailtherapist/2009/11/06/graphic-teacups-to-warm-your-soul/">Graphic Teacups to Warm Your Soul</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dwell.com Product of the Day, November 4th, 2009<br />\r\n	<a href="http://www.dwell.com/products/ceramic-trivets.html">Ceramic Trivets</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Design*Sponge, July 21st, 2009<br />\r\n	<a href="http://www.designspongeonline.com/2009/07/portland-oregon-guide.html">Portland, Oregon Guide</a></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	When I walked into Elsa + Sam, my first thought was “how has no one thought of this before?”. The tiny shop is a bit off the beaten path, but stepping inside was like walking into a showroom of all of the fabulous ceramicists and printers I’ve fawned over for years online but never see in person. Circa Ceramics, Kim Westad, Dovetail, Anna Kraitz, Tonfisk…the list is fantastic, and will have you ready to ditch your dishes in favor of a whole new collection.</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dwell.com Friday Finds, June 12th, 2009<br />\r\n	<a href="http://www.dwell.com/articles/friday-finds-61209.html">Friday Finds 6.12.09</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	OregonLive blog: The Archer, April 21st, 2009<br />\r\n	<a href="http://blog.oregonlive.com/shoporegon/2009/04/elsa_sam_dishware_boutique.html">elsa+sam Dishware Boutique.</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dwell.com, Product of the Day, March 31st 2009<br />\r\n	<a href="http://www.dwell.com/products/porcelain-cylinder.html">Porcelain Cylinder</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Oregon Bride Magazine, Ja