(2111, 2, '2009-10-24 14:04:44', '2009-10-24 19:04:44', 'There is something so satisfying about opening new packages from Circa Ceramics and taking each piece out of the box. It\'s not only their cheerful colors but it\'s the images that make me feel nostalgic. It\'s the same feeling you get when you come across something enjoyable from your past hiding somewhere. You just fall in love with it all over again. Every time I open up a Circa Ceramics package, I have a glee of excitement and am reminded of how awesome and talented they are. \n\n[caption id="attachment_2121" align="alignnone" width="550" caption="Trivet - $26.00"]<img class="size-large wp-image-2121" title="DSC_5641" src="http://blog.elsasam.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/DSC_56412-550x431.jpg" alt="Trivet - $26.00" width="550" height="431" />[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2122" align="alignnone" width="550" caption="Large Bowl - $110"]<img class="size-large wp-image-2122" title="DSC_5676" src="http://blog.elsasam.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/DSC_5676-550x324.jpg" alt="Large Bowl - $110" width="550" height="324" />[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2123" align="alignnone" width="550" caption="Sauce Bowls - $16.00"]<img class="size-large wp-image-2123" title="DSC_5620" src="http://blog.elsasam.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/DSC_56202-550x417.jpg" alt="Sauce Bowls - $16.00" width="550" height="417" />[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2124" align="alignnone" width="550" caption="16oz mugs - $36.00"]<img class="size-large wp-image-2124" title="DSC_5702" src="http://blog.elsasam.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/DSC_5702-550x298.jpg" alt="16oz mugs - $36.00" width="550" height="298" />[/caption] ', 'Circa Ceramics Happiness...', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'circa-ceramics-happiness', '', '', '2009-10-24 14:04:44', '2009-10-24 19:04:44', '', 0, 'http://www.elsasam.com/?p=2111', 0, 'post', '', 5),
(2181, 2, '2009-11-02 13:13:33', '2009-11-02 18:13:33', 'Inspired by her travels around the world, Katy Kidd introduces us to a new way of looking at objects that we tend to throw away or discard. The unique and colorful everyday items painted on layers of acetate give the pieces a subtle depth of field, and remind us that even the most mundane things can be beautiful.\n\nThese pieces and more will be showing through the month of November at elsa+sam. \n\n<img src="http://blog.elsasam.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/kk-brownchairs-tree1-550x458.jpg" alt="kk-brownchairs-tree" title="kk-brownchairs-tree" width="550" height="458" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2192" />\n\n<img src="http://blog.elsasam.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/kk-moths-tires1-340x550.jpg" alt="kk-moths-tires" title="kk-moths-tires" width="340" height="550" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2193" />\n\n<img src="http://blog.elsasam.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/kk-bowls-jerrycans2-364x550.jpg" alt="kk-bowls-jerrycans" title="kk-bowls-jerrycans" width="364" height="550" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2194" />\n\n<img src="http://blog.elsasam.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/kk-fire-bowl-chair-550x351.jpg" alt="kk-fire-bowl-chair" title="kk-fire-bowl-chair" width="550" height="351" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2195" />\n\n<blockquote>\nMy work is a social/environmental commentary on objects from our beauty obsessed, petroleum based, wasteful society. Ubiquitous Objects we label as “tacky”, “garbage”,  “cast aways” or “environmentally harmful” are so prominent in developing countries and are considered useful timesavers, long lasting and in the case of the Jerry Can, a life saver.\n</blockquote>\n\nRead more at <a href="http://www.katykidd.com/">KatyKidd.com</a>.\n\n', 'Santa Fe Artist: Katy Kidd', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'santa-fe-artist-katy-kidd', '', '', '2009-11-02 13:13:33', '2009-11-02 18:13:33', '', 0, 'http://www.elsasam.com/?p=2181', 0, 'post', '', 1) ;
